7 VEHICLE TO HAVE A COMMERCIAL DRIVER'S LICENSE; REQUIRING PERSONS IN A POSITION TO
8 TAKE CONTROL OF PLATOONED VEHICLES TO HAVE A COMMERCIAL DRIVER'S LICENSE;
9 PROVIDING FOR SPECIAL PERMITS REQUIRING A STUDY OF PLATOONING SAFETY BY THE
10 DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION; AND PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; AMENDING
11 SECTION 61-10-124, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN A DELAYED EFFECTIVE DATE.”
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
14
15 (Refer to Introduced Bill)
16 Strike everything after the enacting clause and insert:
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Platooning -- study -- rulemaking. (1) The department of transportation
19 shall complete a feasibility study to determine whether platooning can be safely conducted in Montana. The
20 study must include consideration of Montana's various terrain, weather extremes, effectiveness of supporting
21 communication networks, and any other considerations applicable to the safety of the motoring public.
22 (2) If, upon completion and analysis of the study required in subsection (1), the department
23 determines that platooning can be safely conducted, it shall adopt rules and standards for platooning. Prior to
24 proposing rules on platooning, the department shall engage stakeholders such as members of the
25 transportation interim committee, representatives of law enforcement agencies, the trucking industry, platooning
26 technology developers, ranchers, drivers, pedestrians, tribal governments, and local governments.
27 (3) Platooning may be allowed following the implementation of department rules and standards.
